rComments: Material is interesting for sure. If you take the time to go over the lecture notes you don't even need the textbook. LECTURES ARE A MUST. Tests are straightforward but assignments are marked brutally. Nevertheless, she is a great person and office hours are really helpful.

Test are way too long, assignments are not related to class material and are graded extremely hard. Awful lectures. Material that the textbook easily and clearly explains becomes convoluted and unclear in her lectures. Tests cover every single concept, and all questions require you to give "specific evidence" from papers. Would not recommend.
